
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    `gnome-shell-perf-tool` yek abzar baraye andazegiri va behbood performance (sure'at amal) dar Gnome Shell ast. In abzar komak mikonad ta moshkelate performance ra peyda va bartaraf konid.  Be zabane sade, `gnome-shell-perf-tool` mesle yek doctor baraye Gnome Shell amal mikonad, moshkelat ra tashkhis midehad va rahhal haye dorost kardan anha ra pishnahad mikonad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `--help`   --> ❓Namayesh rahnamaye estefade az abzar.
    🔹 `--verbose`--> 🗣️ Namayesh etela'at bishtar dar morede chگونگی karkarde abzar.
    🔹 `--output=FILE` --> 💾 Zakhire kardan natije andazegiri dar yek file.
    🔹 `--duration=SECONDS` --> ⏳ Tayin moddate zaman baraye andazegiri performance (be sanie).

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ gnome-shell-perf-tool --duration=10

    🔹 Andazegiri performance Gnome Shell baraye 10 sanie.

    $ gnome-shell-perf-tool --output=perf_report.txt

    🔹 Zakhire natije andazegiri performance dar file "perf_report.txt".

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ gnome-shell-perf-tool --duration=5 --verbose

    🔹 Performance Gnome Shell ra baraye 5 sanie andazegiri mikonad va etela'ate bishtar dar morede procces ra namayesh midehad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    `gnome-shell-perf-tool` is a tool for measuring and improving performance in Gnome Shell. It helps identify and fix performance issues. In simple terms, it acts like a doctor for Gnome Shell, diagnosing problems and suggesting solutions.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `--help`   --> ❓ Display help information about using the tool.
    🔹 `--verbose`--> 🗣️ Display more information about how the tool works.
    🔹 `--output=FILE` --> 💾 Save the measurement results to a file.
    🔹 `--duration=SECONDS` --> ⏳ Set the duration for performance measurement (in seconds).

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ gnome-shell-perf-tool --duration=10

    🔹 Measure Gnome Shell performance for 10 seconds.

    $ gnome-shell-perf-tool --output=perf_report.txt

    🔹 Save the performance measurement results to the file "perf_report.txt".

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ gnome-shell-perf-tool --duration=5 --verbose

    🔹 Measures Gnome Shell performance for 5 seconds and displays more information about the process.
